---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About — Eliot Attridge">
  <article class="note-article">
    <header class="note-header">
      <div class="crumbs"><a href="/">Notes</a></div>
      <h1>About</h1>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I'm Eliot. I work across two schools in Marlborough, Aotearoa New Zealand as Director of
        Learning Innovation, in a role that lets me spend my days at the edge where science,
        technology, learning, and human possibility meet. I've been teaching for 30 years, including
        20 as a Head of Science, and I'm still drawn to the places where ideas are being tested,
        remade, and brought to life.
      </p>
      <p>
        My roots are in microbiology, but my working life has wandered quite happily through
        classrooms, curriculum, publishing, and digital innovation. I'm a Fellow of the Royal Society
        of Biology and a Chartered Biologist, and over the years I've written more than 30 books and
        revision resources for the UK education sector, contributed to the Beyond 2000 science
        review, edited ICT reviews for <em>School Science Review</em>, and helped create one of the
        earliest secondary school AI and Robotics courses for Year 9 students. I've been an Adobe
        Education Leader, and I'm now a Microsoft Innovative Educator Expert. Underneath all of that
        is the same enduring interest: how people learn, what sparks curiosity, and what becomes
        possible when knowledge is treated as something living.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is none of those things. It's a thinking space for half-formed ideas, reading
        notes, field observations, and arguments I'm still working out. Notes are allowed to be
        unfinished, contradict each other, and quietly evolve over years. If you want my finished
        writing for learners, educators or budding scientists, that's at
        <a href="https://www.pursuelearning.net">pursuelearning.net</a> or in my published books.
      </p>
      <p>
        Find me at <a href="mailto:drema@eliotattridge.com">drema@eliotattridge.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
